Description:
    Adds a View, Model, or Collection to an app module

Example:
    yo cfsg:mvc

    First choose the module you want to build on. Tip: Use the cfsg:module
    generator to create a new module.

    Then choose whether to create a new Model, Collection, or View, and give it a name.

    Models
    ======
    Adds a JavaScript snippet to:
        /source/js/modules/<ModuleName>.js

    Collections
    ===========
    Adds a JavaScript snippet to:
        /source/js/modules/<ModuleName>.js

    Views
    =====
    Add a JavaScript snippet to:
        /source/js/modules/<ModuleName>.js
    Adds a Handlebars HTML template placeholder to:
        /source/templates/<module-name>/<view-name>.html
    Adds a Stylus CSS placeholder to:
        /source/styles/modules/<module-name>/<view-name>.styl
